      "question": "If I have a disability or special needs, what should I do when applying for UTS Housing?",
      "answer": "If you have a disability or special needs when applying for UTS Housing, you may be given special consideration if your need for UTS accommodation can be linked to your learning needs related to the disability [1]. Additionally, you can seek advice and assistance from the Accessibility Service, which provides support for students with disabilities impacting their studies [2]. It is also helpful to disclose your disability or ongoing medical condition in the 'Accessibility details' section of the \u2018Personal\u2019 tab in My Student Admin to ensure appropriate support is provided [3].",
      "reference": "It is best to let UTS Housing know on your application form. They will then discuss your needs with you and allocate you to an appropriate room.",
