      "question": "What kinds of experiences does UTS say students can get in IT?",
      "answer": "UTS says IT students can gain real-world, hands-on learning experiences from their first semester by solving problems in labs and studios that mirror industry environments. They develop skills that employers want right now and have opportunities to connect with peers and mentors through student societies and support networks. All IT degrees at UTS include internships and industry projects, allowing students to graduate with practical experience and industry contacts, and potentially secure job offers. Additionally, students learn in future-focused environments such as the Cybersecurity Precinct, IT Labs, and Games studio, which are designed for experimentation and collaboration [3][4].",
      "reference": "UTS says IT students can experience cutting-edge labs, design challenges, industry projects, and career pathways. The page also highlights student stories, including paid industry work while studying.",
