      "question": "How does UTS use my personal information, and when can it share it with another organisation?",
      "answer": "UTS uses your personal information to administer student-related programs and activities, such as confirming your identity and eligibility for services like accommodation, managing your course, and supporting your involvement in programs like global mobility [1][3][6]. Your information may also be used for quality improvement and planning processes [6].\n\nUTS can share your personal information with another organisation when you have given consent or when there is a legal obligation to do so. For example, information may be shared with a host university as part of approved arrangements for mobility programs, including details about your application, enrolment, progress, results, and any alleged misconduct [5][6]. UTS also ensures that access to personal information is limited to authorised personnel and takes reasonable steps to securely dispose of information when no longer required, subject to legal retention obligations [2].\n\nYou have the right to access, amend, and update your personal information held by UTS [5].",
      "reference": "UTS collects and uses personal information only when it is necessary and only for the purpose it was collected for. It will share your personal information with another organisation only if you have consented or if there is a legal obligation to do so.",
      "sources": [
        "https://www.uts.edu.au/for-students/current-students/managing-your-course/your-student-info/privacy-and-confidentiality",
