      "question": "Who should I contact if I need academic advice about my course of study, major, or progression that the Student Centre can't provide?",
      "answer": "If you need academic advice about your course of study, major, or progression that the Student Centre can't provide, you should contact the Program Coordinator for your major or course. For long-term circumstances affecting your studies, consult the relevant Academic Liaison Officer in your faculty [3]. Additionally, for subject-specific questions, you can initially speak with your lecturer or tutor, and if needed, the Subject Coordinator whose contact details are in the subject outline on Canvas [4][6].",
      "reference": "Academic advice that the Student Centre is unable to provide is available from program directors, also known as Academic Advisers.",
