      "question": "What support is available if I'm struggling with wellbeing, money, or housing as a UTS student?",
      "answer": "If you are struggling with wellbeing, money, or housing as a UTS student, there are several free and confidential support services available to you. For wellbeing, UTS offers free counselling for study-related, personal, psychological, and administrative difficulties, as well as practical help to manage time and balance study, work, and life [3]. For financial difficulties, the UTS Financial Assistance Service provides confidential appointments, small grants, interest-free loans, grocery vouchers, housing subsidies, and digital access support [3][6]. For housing support, UTS also offers services to assist students with accommodation needs [3][4]. You are encouraged to seek help early to access these supports [1][5].",
      "reference": "UTS offers free and confidential support for wellbeing, money and housing. This includes counselling, financial advice and short-term loans, food and basic supplies, and help with UTS residences, private or share accommodation, and tenancy matters.",
