      "question": "What kind of help can the International Student Centre give current international students?",
      "answer": "The International Student Centre at UTS provides a wide range of support for current international students, including help with issues affecting your study, extending your study and applying for a new Confirmation of Enrolment (CoE), reducing your study load or taking Leave of Absence, and other issues when you don't know who to talk to, as the student advisers can help you find the right service [4]. They also offer official documents, support for general visa enquiries, and can connect you with the right services if you have problems that might prevent you from completing your course successfully [3][5]. You can contact them by phone, email, or visit the centre in person from 9am to 5pm, Monday to Friday [5][6].",
      "reference": "The International Student Centre can provide official documents to prove your status as a UTS student, such as a Confirmation of Enrolment (CoE), student verification letter, and statement of course completion. It can also help with residency status changes, general student visa issues, and other study-related issues if you're not sure who to talk to.",
