      "question": "What does digital finance mean in the article?",
      "answer": "Digital finance in the article refers to using technology to create entirely new types of markets where anything of value can be exchanged digitally. It is not just about moving money online but redefining who can invest, what can be traded, and how markets operate. Key components include blockchain, a shared and decentralised digital ledger recording all digital trades, and smart contracts, which are small computer programs on the blockchain that automatically execute deals when conditions are met, eliminating middlemen and delays. Digital finance enables cheaper, borderless, transparent trading accessible to investors from all walks of life. It also involves tokenisation, which is the digital representation of physical and financial assets, powering digital finance markets [1][3][4].",
