      "question": "What do I need to be eligible to be considered for admission to UTS, and are there other requirements for some courses?",
      "answer": "To be eligible to be considered for admission to UTS, you must:  \n- Be eligible to matriculate  \n- Meet English language requirements  \n- Have an assessable qualification (for example, an ATAR or IB) [1][3][4]\n\nAdditionally, some UTS courses have other requirements such as:  \n- Compulsory selection criteria, which must be submitted on time for your application to be considered  \n- Optional selection criteria, which can improve your chances of selection through admissions schemes  \n- Course-specific additional criteria, such as an interview, test, or other assessments [3][4]\n\nIt is important to check your specific course information page to confirm any special or additional requirements before applying [1][2][6].",
