      "answer": "Yes, your previous study at another university or TAFE can count towards recognition of prior learning (RPL) for a Design, Architecture, or Built Environment course at UTS. The Faculty of Design, Architecture and Building has a list of approved exemptions for several TAFE courses and UTS College, known as articulated courses, which may qualify for RPL. Your previous studies must meet the requirements set out in the UTS Student Rules and the Faculty's RPL guidelines to be considered [1][5].",
      "reference": "Yes. If you have studied these subject areas at an Australian university, international university, UTS College, TAFE, or another college or institution, you can apply for recognition of prior learning (RPL). RPL is granted subject to UTS Student Rules and UTS DAB RPL guidelines.",
