      "question": "How much does the Guangzhou Winter School cost, and are there any scholarships available?",
      "answer": "The Guangzhou Winter School program costs depend on your accommodation preference:  \n- Twin hotel room: $3,308 total program fee  \n- Single hotel room: $4,050 total program fee  \n\nThis fee covers academic lectures, accommodation at a 4-star hotel (Easeland Hotel Guangzhou), inner-city and intra-city transportation, airport shuttles, 3 meals each day, and events such as an opening ceremony and farewell banquet hosted by GDUFS [3][4].\n\nRegarding scholarships, eligible students may receive up to $3,000 in scholarships. There are 15 Dean\u2019s Mobility Scholarships worth $2,000 each and 10 Global Short Programs Travel Scholarships worth $1,000 each. Scholarships are allocated based on academic merit and motivation, with priority given to students from an equity background [3].",
      "reference": "The total program fee is $3,308 for a twin hotel room or $4,050 for a single hotel room. Eligible students may receive up to $3,000 in scholarships, including 15 Dean\u2019s Mobility Scholarships of $2,000 and 10 Global Short Programs Travel Scholarships of $1,000.",
