      "question": "How can I make it easier to get into study mode when I sit down to work?",
      "answer": "To make it easier to get into study mode when you sit down to work, you can:\n\n- Set up a consistent space and time for studying so your brain automatically switches to study mode when you are in that environment or at that time [2].\n- Create rituals that signal to your brain it\u2019s time to focus, which can also inform others around you that you are concentrating [2].\n- Start with a small, manageable task, such as telling yourself you will study for just five minutes to build momentum and motivation to continue [1].\n- Organise your study into timed blocks, for example, studying for 50 minutes followed by a 10-minute break, which can make study sessions more productive and sustainable [5].\n- Use your phone\u2019s settings to set time limits or designate specific days for app access to reduce distractions [3][4].\n\nThese strategies help your brain transition into study mode more easily and maintain focus [1][2][3][4][5].",
      "reference": "Establishing a consistent routine can help your brain switch to study mode more automatically. Setting up the same space and time to study, along with rituals like turning off your phone, using a calendar, listening to particular music, or time blocking, can help you start concentrating.",
