    {
      "question": "In a reflective task, what should I write about how the experience will affect what I do in the future?",
      "answer": "In a reflective task, when writing about how the experience will affect what you do in the future, you should describe what you plan to change as a result of the experience and reflection you have done, or what you would do differently if a similar situation occurs again. For example, you might explain how you will apply new tools or strategies learned, such as using the SMART goal approach in future projects to have a clearer idea of your objectives and plans [1]. This is part of the \"Now what?\" stage in reflective writing, where you outline your action plan and how you will develop skills to handle similar situations better [2][3].",
      "reference": "You should describe what you plan to change as a result of the experience and your reflection, or what you would do differently if a similar situation happened again. The example given says to use the SMART goal approach in future projects to help clarify what you want to achieve and how you will achieve it.",
