      "question": "What kinds of experiences can I get at UTS to help me become career-ready?",
      "answer": "At UTS, you can gain a variety of experiences to help you become career-ready, including:\n\n- Volunteering activities that help you gain experience and develop leadership skills [1].\n- Participating in events organized by Activate UTS such as barbecues, performances, sports, trivia, and joining one of over 180 clubs covering cultural, political, religious, social, and sporting interests [1].\n- Engaging in real-world problem solving, networking opportunities, internships, and social justice initiatives, especially within business-related programs [2].\n- Accessing UTS Careers services, which support you in exploring career paths, building skills, meeting employers, and connecting with work opportunities during and after your degree [4].\n- Using the online careers platform CareerHub to find jobs and internships [4].\n- Signing up for professional mentoring and receiving resume advice and feedback from Peer Career Advisors [3].\n- Collaborating with other students and investigating real-world issues as part of your learning experience, which helps you acquire important professional attributes [5].\n- Building your skills and community through leadership development, volunteering, sports, and social activities [6].\n\nThese opportunities collectively prepare you practically and professionally for your future career [1][2][3][4][5][6].",
