      "question": "What are reporting verbs used for in academic writing?",
      "answer": "Reporting verbs in academic writing are used to cite original sources when using others\u2019 ideas, helping to present information clearly. They allow you to express your stance on the sourced information and strengthen your arguments in assignments. Additionally, reporting verbs help show your attitude towards the source of information you are citing, whether positive, negative, or neutral. They are an important tool for evaluating the quality of ideas and developing critical thinking skills [1][2][4][6].",
