    {
      "question": "What does critical writing involve, and how is it different from descriptive writing?",
      "answer": "Critical writing involves analysing information to understand a problem or topic from more than one perspective, making logical connections between ideas, and offering your own perspective on the topic based on your evaluation of the available evidence [1]. Unlike descriptive writing, which simply states what happened, critical writing identifies the significance of what happened, explains situations, questions existing explanations, examines alternative explanations, evaluates evidence, and aims to provide the writer\u2019s perspective to encourage deeper thinking [1][3][4].",
      "reference": "Critical writing involves analysing information from more than one perspective, making logical connections between ideas, and offering your own perspective based on the available evidence. Unlike descriptive writing, it goes beyond stating or listing information by evaluating significance, evidence, and alternative explanations.",
