      "question": "What do I need to do to keep my US Financial Aid while I'm studying at UTS?",
      "answer": "To keep your US Financial Aid while studying at UTS, you must:\n\n1. Maintain full-time enrolment, which is 24 UTS credit points per semester, in accordance with Australian student visa conditions [1].  \n2. Make satisfactory academic progress as per UTS academic progression rules [1][5].  \n3. Not enrol in subjects or degrees offered by online or telecommunication delivery [1].  \n4. Reapply for your US Financial Aid every year by completing a new FAFSA, a new UTS Financial Aid Application, and a new Master Promissory Note (MPN) online at Federal Student Aid, then submit your completed UTS Financial Aid Application and a copy of your Student Aid Report (SAR) to UTS [4].  \n5. Be enrolled at least half-time (12 credit points per semester) to be eligible, though full-time enrolment (24 credit points) is normally expected [5].",
