      "question": "If my leave of absence is approved, what changes to my fees and campus access should I expect?",
      "answer": "If your leave of absence is approved, your tuition fees liability will be adjusted to take into account your leave of absence, provided your application was made on or before the census date of the relevant teaching period. Any credit balance of relevant tuition fees previously paid will be refunded to you [1]. \n\nThe context does not provide specific information about changes to campus access during a leave of absence.",
      "reference": "If your application was made on or before the census date, your tuition fees liability will be adjusted for the leave of absence and any credit balance of relevant tuition fees previously paid will be refunded. During your leave, you won\u2019t have access to UTS campus or facilities, the UTS Library (including electronic resources), CareerHub or GITLab, and you\u2019re no longer entitled to a travel concession.",
