      "question": "Am I eligible to apply for the Commonwealth Prac Payment if I'm a UTS student in teaching, nursing, or midwifery?",
      "answer": "You may be eligible to apply for the Commonwealth Prac Payment (CPP) if you meet the following criteria:\n\n- You are a domestic student (Australian citizen, New Zealand citizen, dual citizen of Australia or New Zealand, or Australian permanent resident visa holder) [2][6].\n- You are enrolled in a Commonwealth Supported Place (CSP) [6].\n- You are completing a Bachelor\u2019s or Master\u2019s degree in an eligible program of study that leads to entry-to-practice in teaching, nursing, or midwifery [6].\n- You are undertaking a mandatory practicum placement on a full-time basis (minimum 30 hours per week) linked to the same field of education as your degree [6].\n- You meet one of the financial criteria, such as being on a Commonwealth income support payment (e.g., ABSTUDY, Austudy, Youth Allowance, or DVA Education Allowance) [5].\n\nIf you meet these conditions, you can apply for the Commonwealth Prac Payment to support your practicum placements [1][2].",
      "reference": "If you\u2019re a domestic student studying teaching, nursing or midwifery, you may be eligible to apply for a Commonwealth government payment to support your prac placements. The payment is intended to help with ongoing costs while you complete mandatory practical placements.",
