      "question": "What is the difference between study abroad and exchange at UTS?",
      "answer": "The difference between study abroad and exchange at UTS is as follows:\n\n- **Study Abroad** is open to students from any recognised university or college, including those who have completed high school. Students pay fees directly to UTS. You can apply via a UTS student recruitment agent or at your International Office if you study at a UTS study abroad partner institution [1].\n\n- **Exchange** is open to students who are enrolled at a UTS exchange partner institution and must be nominated by their home university. Exchange students remain enrolled full-time at their home university while studying at UTS and receive credit towards their degree [1][3][6].\n\nIn summary, study abroad is generally for fee-paying students from any university, while exchange is for nominated students from partner institutions who study at UTS with credit towards their home degree [1][3][6].",
