    {
      "question": "Why should I study Urban Planning at UTS?",
      "answer": "You should study Urban Planning at UTS because it offers a multidisciplinary approach to designing sustainable, functional, and aesthetically pleasing urban environments, preparing you to contribute meaningfully to the future of cities and communities [1]. UTS provides a unique learning experience in the heart of a thriving urban city, combining core subjects like planning, sustainable development, and urban design with human-centred skills such as negotiation and community engagement [2]. The program is accredited and well-connected with industry, helping you become an industry leader or advance your career [2][3]. Additionally, studying on campus offers interactive learning, hands-on experience through fieldwork, site visits, and studio projects [4]. Sydney itself acts as a living laboratory, allowing you to engage with real-world urban challenges and collaborate with professionals [5]. Overall, UTS positions you at the forefront of a growing and dynamic industry with strong career prospects [5][6].",
      "reference": "UTS says there is growing demand for urban planning professionals, with shortages in almost every state and territory. The industry is expected to grow by 2,500 jobs by 2026, creating many job opportunities.",
      "sources": [
        "https://www.uts.edu.au/for-students/experience-uts/design-architecture-and-building/faqs-studying-urban-planning-at-uts",
