    {
      "question": "What can a Sport and Exercise Science degree prepare me for?",
      "answer": "A Sport and Exercise Science degree can prepare you for a wide range of roles in the sport, recreation, health, and fitness sectors. Sport-related roles include sports scientist, high performance manager, performance analyst, strength and conditioning coach, exercise physiologist, exercise scientist, biomechanist, athlete management, sports coach or manager, sport marketing, and sport development. Health and fitness roles include personal trainer and group fitness instructor [1]. \n\nAdditionally, the degree helps combine your interest in health promotion and physical fitness with working with people, preparing you to deliver sport and exercise activities across all community segments [2]. It can also lead to further qualifications in clinical exercise physiology, physiotherapy, and high-performance sports [5].",
      "reference": "A Sport and Exercise Science degree can prepare you for life on and beyond the field. The text says it can lead to areas like coaching, athlete management, and the science of human movement.",
      "sources": [
        "https://www.uts.edu.au/for-students/current-students/managing-your-course/current-students-information-health/information-current-sport-and-exercise-students",
