      "question": "What skills will I develop in the Juris Doctor, and can it lead to non-legal careers too?",
      "answer": "In the Juris Doctor at UTS, you will develop practical, pragmatic, and industry-focused skills that prepare you for a variety of career paths. The course helps you gain critical foundational knowledge and capabilities needed for a career in Australian law, but also equips you with skills that are applicable beyond traditional legal roles. Many students have found that the Juris Doctor has helped them leverage their experience into new and diverse career paths, including starting businesses or working in fields like technology and health. The pathways after completing the Juris Doctor are described as limitless, showing its broad applicability to both legal and non-legal careers [1][2][3][5][6].",
      "reference": "The Juris Doctor helps you develop advanced professional skills such as critical thinking, communication and problem-solving. It can support a successful legal or non-legal career.",
