      "question": "What is the census date at UTS?",
      "answer": "The census date at UTS is the last day to withdraw from a subject without incurring academic penalty and financial liability. It is also the date on which you become financially liable for any subjects in which you are enrolled [1][3]. \n\nFor example, in 2026, the census dates are:\n- Thursday 21 May 2026 for the session commencing 11 May 2026\n- Thursday 16 July 2026 for the session commencing 6 July 2026 [2][6].",
