      "question": "What do UTS Business Mentors do for students?",
      "answer": "UTS Business Mentors provide individualised support to students through six sessions over the semester, helping with study skills, networking, major/subject selection, extra-curricular opportunities, and professional development [1]. They guide students on class activities by being embedded in tutorials and workshops and share experiences on doing well at university and life beyond [2].",
