      "question": "How many supervisors are on a UTS HDR student\u2019s supervisory panel, and can one of them be external to UTS?",
      "answer": "A UTS HDR student\u2019s supervisory panel consists of a minimum of two supervisors: a principal supervisor and at least one co-supervisor. The panel may also include additional co-supervisors, assistant supervisors, or external supervisors. One of the supervisors, such as an alternate or co-supervisor, may be external to UTS, but the principal supervisor must be an internal tenured academic staff member with qualifications equivalent to the degree they are supervising [1][2][3][5].",
