    {
      "question": "What is studying architecture at UTS like?",
      "answer": "Studying architecture at UTS offers a blend of creativity and practicality, allowing students to develop a wide range of skills including technical knowledge, design, visualisation, project management, problem solving, and communication. The program is innovative and comprehensive, covering subjects from design and technology to history and theory, with a curriculum that evolves to reflect the latest trends and advancements in the field, ensuring graduates have current and relevant knowledge [3][5].\n\nUTS provides face-to-face architecture courses on campus, which include real-time interaction with faculty and peers, hands-on experience through studio projects and site visits, and opportunities for networking with classmates and industry professionals. Students also have access to state-of-the-art facilities [1].\n\nStudying architecture at UTS is described as a rigorous blend of concept, critique, and creativity, helping students build strong portfolios and gain industry experience. The program supports a mix of technical understanding and excellent visual communication to effectively convey ideas and real-world experience with industry partners [6].\n\nAdditionally, being located in the heart of Sydney offers daily exposure to a vibrant urban environment rich in culture and direct industry connections, enhancing the learning experience [4].",
      "reference": "Studying architecture is very hands on, involving making and drawing. It is a very different kind of degree and is very creative.",
      "sources": [
        "https://www.uts.edu.au/for-students/experience-uts/design-architecture-and-building/faqs-studying-architecture-uts",
